New Records: David Willey reached 100 one-day international wickets
Chris Woakes broke Ian Botham's England record for most World Cup wickets with 31
Key Match Events: Jonny Bairstow and Ben Stokes put on an opening stand of 82
Adil Rashid bowled Saud Shakeel and Shadab Khan
David Willey dismissed Abdullah Shafique lbw first ball
Fakhar Zaman chipped to mid-off for one
Chris Woakes took the wicket of Mohammad Wasim Jr and Mohammad Rauf
Miscellaneous Highlights: England finished the World Cup in seventh place
The match was played at the iconic Eden Gardens in Kolkata
The match was played in anticipation for Diwali
Others: Eoin Morgan, who is no longer the captain, was on the sidelines
Jos Buttler played down talk of a 'clearout' after the match
Matthew Mott, the head coach, made it sound like a number of changes were coming
